<title>USA: Yamaichi seen ripe for foreign alliance - WSJ.</title>
<headline>Yamaichi seen ripe for foreign alliance - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Legal troubles at Yamaichi Securities Co might drive the company into a merger with another securities firm in a worst case scenerio, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing analysts.</p>
<p>The paper in its electronic edition said such a merger might be with a foreign partner or a Japanese bank.</p>
<p>The paper said that any foreign partnership might be similar to the agreement Long Term Credit Bank of Japan recently worked out with Swiss Bank Corp.</p>
<p>Yamaichi is suspected of making payoffs to alleged racketeer Ryuichi Koike, who has been charged with extorting money from some Japanese banks, the paper said.</p>
